title: Notes from "Professional: JavaScript® for Web Developers"

textRun.content: This document is overwritten when you make changes in Play Books.
You should make a copy of this document before you edit it.
The concept of execution context, referred to as context for simplicity, is of the utmost importance in JavaScript.
Certain statements cause a temporary addition to the front of the scope chain that is later removed after code execution.
In JavaScript, however, the variable declaration adds a variable into the current execution context (the global context, in this case).
